{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## S2 implemented + deployed LIVE on i-00880b2c7f13527c5 — 2026-06-30 (commit 6cd6f4e1f)\n\n**Stack:** docker-compose runs gerrit (gerritcodereview/gerrit:3.14.1, arm64) + the review-bot (FastAPI). Host nginx terminates TLS and proxies; host certbot manages the cert.\n\n**AC verification (all live-verified):**\n- Gerrit reachable at https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/ with a valid Let's Encrypt cert (issuer Let's Encrypt, curl ssl_verify_result=0); `/config/server/version` -> 200 \"3.14.1\".\n- %2F round-trip: a request to `/projects/test%2Fencoded` appears in Gerrit httpd_log as `test%2Fencoded` (NOT decoded to `test/encoded`) — nginx bare `proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080;` preserves the encoded slash end-to-end.\n- certbot renewal automated: systemd `certbot-renew.timer` enabled (twice daily, nginx-reload deploy-hook); `certbot renew --dry-run` -> \"Congratulations, all simulated renewals succeeded\". nginx :80 serves /.well-known/acme-challenge/.\n- Gerrit SSH on 29418 works: `ssh -p29418 admin@host gerrit version` -> 3.14.1; `git clone ssh://admin@host:29418/All-Projects` succeeds. Admin (account 1000000, Administrators) bootstrapped; SSH key registered via NoteDb (refs/users/00/1000000 authorized_keys).\n- Data persists across `docker compose down`/`up` AND an instance reboot: stateful site subdirs are bind-mounted from the EBS data volume (/var/gerrit/site/{git,index,cache,db,etc,logs,plugins}); the admin account + SSH key survived multiple down/up cycles (re-cloned successfully). Bind mounts on the EBS volume are inherently safe from `docker compose down -v` (which only removes named volumes).\n- review-bot reachable through nginx at /review/: GET /review/health -> 200 {\"status\":\"ok\"}; POST /review/webhook -> 202 (reaches the receiver process, not a 502).\n- Secrets from SSM via fetch-secrets.sh into a 0600, gitignored, ephemeral .env (instance role, IMDSv2, fail-fast on unreachable/empty/CHANGEME). LLM path enabled by ANTHROPIC_API_KEY + [agents]; REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM NOT set. **.dockerignore added** so the .env/.git never bake into the image layer (verified absent in the built image).\n- IAM SSM read scoped to parameter/rebar/prod/* (S1; S2 adds no extra IAM — iam_s2.tf is a documentation anchor).\n- Both containers log to journald (verified `logging.driver: journald`); health probe (/, /review/health) via systemd timer rebar-observability.timer logging to journald; CloudWatch disk-usage alarm `rebar-gerrit-data-disk-high` (>=85% of /var/gerrit) created.\n- Gerrit at an existing arm64 patch tag 3.14.1, heapLimit=2g, packedGitLimit=1g budgeted OFF-heap.\n\n**Non-obvious fixes during live bring-up (all folded into the repo):**\n- The official image runs from /var/gerrit and ignores GERRIT_SITE -> persist stateful SUBDIRS (not the whole site) so baked binaries aren't shadowed.\n- gerrit.sh infinite-loops on modern JDK (no lib/tools.jar) unless container.javaHome is set; init sets it on first boot but a full-file config re-seed clobbered it -> gerrit.config is now self-sufficient (javaHome + javaOptions + basePath + serverId pinned).\n- Cookie-auth REST mutations are blocked (no obtainable XSRF/HTTP password from a clean slate) -> admin SSH key registered deterministically via NoteDb.\n- Gerrit proxy redirect-loop avoided via Host $host + X-Forwarded-Proto https + proxy-https listenUrl + matching canonicalWebUrl.\n\n**Code review (subagent):** 2 blockers — missing .dockerignore (secrets baked into image) and bootstrap aborting on a fresh NoteDb user branch — both FIXED and verified (image has no .env/.git; bootstrap now dev-logins to create the account then guards the fetch). Nits (stale comment, empty-SSM guard) addressed.\n\nPlugin install + bot identity/event wiring are S4a; receiver review/vote LOGIC is S4b (S2 ships the skeleton)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782786736433549001,"uuid":"59e43c11-a92a-4105-ae4f-fee126814d64"}